; From the [ArchWiki on System time](https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/System_time)
; When dual booting Windows and Linux, it is recommended that Windows
; use UTC so the time is correct in both systems.
; This .reg file makes the necessary changes to the Windows registry
; to have Windows use UTC.
Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\TimeZoneInformation]
"RealTimeIsUniversal"=dword:00000001
